    description:
      '<p><strong>COMING SOON...</strong></p><p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px \'Helvetica Neue\'; color: #000000">Luxury and lifestyle intersect in this beautifully renovated loft-style apartment. We are located at 99V Airport/Airpark, uniquely nestled along the base of the West Elks Range of the Rockies. We sit squarely on a plateau along the North Rim of the Black Canyon of the Gunnison National Park, tucked in the North Fork Valley of the Western Slope of Colorado.<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>Our valley sits with a view to the north of the Grand Mesa, which is the largest flat top mesa mountain in the world. This valley allows access to<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>state parks, national parks, national forest, as well as local wineries and farm to table food options.</p><p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px \'Helvetica Neue\'; color: #000000">This updated apartment is done in mountain rustic style. It has it’s own private patio and entrance along the west side of the hangar. The patio features a sitting area and BBQ. Enter into the downstairs sitting-room vestibule that captures a glimpse of the indoor hangar. This area offers storage and a cozy workspace. Stroll upstairs and enter through a salon style swing door into the apartment at large. This open concept apartment flows around the 180 degree backdrop vista of Grand Mesa to Land’s End. Beautiful tile, quartz countertops, modern appliances and cozy accommodations abound. The open flow has a separate private bedroom with a King bed or 2 XL twins and laundry niche. The living room offers an additional queen sized futon. The kitchen is adequately stocked to accommodate a comfortable stay. An L-shaped breakfast bar adjoins the kitchen and living space. The bathroom is right off the living space with a rock bottom walk-in shower.</p><p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px \'Helvetica Neue\'; color: #000000">Hangar Hideaway offers great privacy and enjoyment…a spectacular retreat destination.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br class="Apple-interchange-newline">',
